==English==
===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|ja|櫓||tower, turret, keep, scaffold}}.
===Noun===
{{en-noun|yagura}}
# {{lb|en|sumo}} A high [[wooden]] [[tower]] in front of a [[sumo]] [[arena]] from which a [[yobidashi]] beats the [[taiko]] [[drum]] each day before and after each [[tournament]].
